('Chinese New Year Celebration Firecrakers','The Firecracker Ceremony takes place on the actual Lunar New Year and is a smaller celebration, while the larger NYC Lunar New Year Parade will follow a few weeks later on February 25, 2024. The Firecracker Ceremony & Cultural Festival will feature firecrackers, fireworks and lion dancers. The event is FREE to attend.','February 10, 2024','Manhattan','Holiday Event', true, 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1577794678468-b52b7d867388?q=80&w=1530&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D', 'https://betterchinatown.com/'),
('Chinese Lunar New Year Parade', 'Festival booths are on Bayard Street between Mott and Mulberry Streets. The parade route is as follows - Begins at Mott & Canal to Chatham Square to East Broadway towards the Manhattan Bridge, completing on Eldridge and Forsyth Streets towards Grand Street next to Sara D. Roosevelt Park.','February 25, 2024','Manhattan', 'Parade',true,'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1707716489310-0bee7330ff6b?q=80&w=1470&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D','https://betterchinatown.com/lny-parade/'),
('The Harlem Renaissance and Transatlanic Modernian, at the MET', 'A new exhibition coming to The Metropolitan Museum of Art will whisk visitors back in time a century. Titled The Harlem Renaissance and Transatlantic Modernism, the exhibit will present 160 works exploring how Black artists portrayed everyday modern life in the new Black cities that took shape in the 1920s-40s in New York City’s Harlem, Chicago’s South Side and nationwide amid the Great Migratio','February 25th - July 28, 2024','Manhattan','Art Exhibt',true,'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576838240759-7c6d550263d7?q=80&w=1442&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D','https://www.metmuseum.org/exhibitions/the-harlem-renaissance-and-transatlantic-modernism'),
