('Japan Food Festival','is a Japanese festival that has found its home in New York. It is renowned as the world''s largest Japanese food festival, attracting over 300,000 visitors annually and hosting more than 21 events throughout the year, featuring 1,000 vendors.','March 23, 2024','Manhattan','Food Event',true,'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1602273660127-a0000560a4c1?q=80&w=1472&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D','https://www.japanfes.com/'),
('The Macy''s Flower Show','The annual ode to springtime is in full bloom at Macy''s Herald Square in 2024, with thousands of stunning flowers & lush plants transforming the flagship store into one of the most colorful destinations in NYC','March 24 - April 6, 2024','Manhattan','Spring Event', true,'https://offloadmedia.feverup.com/secretnyc.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/25075618/Macys-Flower-Show-2023-1024x683.jpg','https://www.macys.com/s/flower-show/'),
('International Auto Show at the Javits Center','There is no better place to research your next new car than the New York Auto Show. For more than a century New Yorker’s have visited the show in the millions to experience everything that the automobile industry has to offer and to get a glimpse into the future. It’s the one place where the information is comprehensive and engaging and where new technology can be explained and explored freely.','March 29 - April 7, 2024','Manhattan', 'Auto Show', false,'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1572299250382-3f08d3645b2b?q=80&w=1470&auto=format&fit=crop&ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D','https://www.autoshowny.com/' ),
('Easter & Easter Bonnet Parade','The parade takes place along 5th Avenue from 49th to 57th Streets with the epicenter in front of St Patrick''s Cathedral. It''s more of a milling about in bonnets and Easter outfits, than it is a real parade. More like a themed costume party.','March 31, 2024','Manhattan','Parade',true,'https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f2ecc8594a1d33040f8464a/1596922815169-W5HVHN1QNBYLHOP9HV8Q/image-asset.jpeg','https://www.nyctourism.com/events/easter-parade-and-easter-bonnet-festival1/'),
('United Airline NYC Half','Experience the bright lights of New York City as the United Airlines NYC Half returns on Sunday, March 17, 2024! The 13.1-mile journey begins in Brooklyn, making its way over the historic Manhattan Bridge and FDR Drive. Runners also get the unique opportunity to run through Times Square (only 1 of 2 times that it is closed each year!) and finish in Central Park.','March 17, 2024','Citywide','Marathon',false,'https://prodsitecore.blob.core.windows.net/nyrrsitecoreblob/nyrr/image/photogallery/2024/uanych-finish-gallery/023_nych24_sameday_dpl_215-2.jpg','https://www.nyrr.org/races/2024unitedairlinesnychalf');
